   <text>
      <body xml:id="del">
         <div>
            <head>del</head>
            <p>
               <list>
                  <item>A) something was deleted because it was incorrect: for example erroneously written twice (dittography) or superfluous characters
               </item><item>B) for other reasons like former names of former owners of the manuscript.
    </item></list>           
              
              E.g. 
               <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                  <hi rend="rubric">ነዓ፡ ኀቤየ፡ ኦእግዚእየ፡ 
                     ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ወልደ፡ 
                     እግዚአ</hi><del 
                        rend="expunctuated" 
                        cause="dittography">እግዚአ</del>ብሔር፡ 
                  ሕያው። ወወልደ፡ <hi rend="rubric">ማርያም፡</hi> 
                  ሥግው። መ<del rend="effaced" cause="superfluous">ለ</del>ብረቀ፡ 
                  <hi rend="rubric">መለኮት፡</hi> መደንግፅ። ፍሕ
               </egXML>
            </p>
               <p>The values of <att>rend</att> can be multiple, so you can improve the example above by adding more than one value, like in the following example for <ref type="figure" target="#example1"></ref>.</p>
               <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                  <del rend="expunctuated effaced">እግዚአ</del>
               </egXML>
            <figure>
               <graphic xml:id="example1" url="https://betamasaheft.eu/iiif/guidelines/del/3.tif/info.json">
                  <desc>letters expunctuated (surrounded by dots) for deletion</desc></graphic>
            </figure>
            
            <p>The value 'expunctuated' can be used also for cases like <ref type="figure" target="#example2"></ref> lines above and below are used for the same purpose.</p>
            <figure>
               <graphic xml:id="example2" url="https://betamasaheft.eu/iiif/guidelines/del/2.tif/info.json">
                  <desc>letters with lines above and below</desc></graphic>
            </figure>
            <p><ref type="figure" target="#example3"></ref> is an example of encircled letters.</p>
            
            <figure>
               <graphic xml:id="example3" url="https://betamasaheft.eu/iiif/guidelines/del/1.tif/info.json">
                  <desc>encircled letters, sometimes due to optimizing the pen movement for lines above and below</desc></graphic>
            </figure>
            
         </div>
